This paper is primarily focused on designing a scalable parallel SVM training algorithm for large scale systems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses techniques for improving time-space complexity, which could fall under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on various datasets, which could fall under the categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
